  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p><p>Add the <strong>Cumberland</strong> <strong>sausages</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606304162299-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606304162299-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606304162299-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606304162299-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1606304162299-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>(as finely as you can!)</p><p>Grate the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on)</p><p>Add the <strong>grated potato </strong>and <strong>sliced shallot </strong>to the middle of a tea towel with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring the four corners together to form a ball, twist the ball and squeeze out as much liquid as you can – this is your <strong>potato mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606304173163-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606304173163-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606304173163-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606304173163-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1606304173163-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>chives </strong>finely</p><p>Add the <strong>potato</strong> <strong>mixture</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix up</p><p>Separate the mixture into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> and shape into rough <strong>potato cakes</strong>, about 1cm thick</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606304181978-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606304181978-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606304181978-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606304181978-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1606304181978-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>potato cakes</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side until golden and crispy</p><p>Once done, add them to a plate and set aside – these are your <strong>hash browns</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606304190443-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606304190443-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606304190443-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606304190443-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1606304190443-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>tomatoes </strong>in half</p><p>Once the hash browns are done, add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>tomato </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side until browned and softened</p><p>Once done, add them to the plate with the hash browns and set aside</p><p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1606304198352-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1606304198352-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1606304198352-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1606304198352-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1606304198352-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausages are done, remove them from the oven and allow to cool</p><p>Slice the <strong>ciabatta rolls</strong> in half, then add them to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until they're hot and crusty</p><p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304211524-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304211524-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304211524-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1606304211524-x1000.jpg",
